id: pm-bkvx
title: Linked-test sandbox project/global extension parity
description: Make linked-test sandbox execution load both project and global extension/settings context so extension-defined item types validate identically to workspace runs.
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: custom-types,extensions,linked-tests,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-04-03T22:53:26.793Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-04T17:38:47.398Z"
deadline: "2026-04-13T22:53:26.793Z"
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 300
acceptance_criteria: Linked commands executed via pm test and pm test-all accept extension-defined type filters that are valid in direct workspace commands for both project and global extension roots.
definition_of_ready: Epic pm-mf5z exists and parity implementation files/tests identified.
order: 2
goal: Linked test reliability
objective: Restore extension-defined type parity in linked sandboxes
value: Eliminates contradictory custom-type validation between direct and linked commands
impact: Improves correctness of governance evidence in extension-enabled repositories
outcome: Linked sandbox mirrors project/global extension behavior for type validation
why_now: User-reported pm-lvej and pm-6fmt regressions block reliable automation in custom-schema projects.
